<LegalLayout title="Privacy — NoVibe" heading="Privacy">
  <p>
    This site is built to collect as little as possible. It uses no cookies, no
    analytics, no tracking, and no advertising. Fonts are self-hosted, so loading
    the page sends no data to third-party font services (such as Google Fonts).
  </p>

  <h2>Who is responsible</h2>
  <p>
    The data controller for this website is Stefan St&uuml;hrmann, Portugal. For any
    privacy request, contact <a href="mailto:stefan@novibe.org">stefan@novibe.org</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Hosting and server logs</h2>
  <p>
    This site is hosted by GitHub Pages (GitHub, Inc., 88 Colin P. Kelly Jr.
    Street, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA). When you visit, GitHub automatically
    processes technical data &mdash; including your IP address and request
    metadata &mdash; in server logs, in order to deliver the site reliably and
    securely. We do not control or receive these logs.
  </p>
  <p>
    Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in operating the site
    securely). Data may be transferred to the USA under GitHub&rsquo;s data
    protection framework; see GitHub&rsquo;s
    <a href="https://docs.github.com/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement"
      >Privacy Statement</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h2>No personal data collected by us</h2>
  <p>
    We do not run forms, accounts, newsletters, or any server of our own. We do
    not knowingly store any personal data about you beyond the hosting logs
    described above.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>Under the GDPR you have the right to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>access, rectification, and erasure of your data;</li>
    <li>restriction of, and objection to, processing;</li>
    <li>data portability;</li>
    <li>
      lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority &mdash; in Portugal, the
      CNPD (<a href="https://www.cnpd.pt">cnpd.pt</a>).
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p class="meta">
    Template &mdash; replace the placeholders in brackets. This is general
    information, not legal advice. Last updated: 15 June 2026.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
